Source: hpklinux
Section: sound
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Alban Peignier <alban.peignier@free.fr>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>> 4.0.0)
Standards-Version: 3.6.2

Package: hpklinux-module-_KVERS_
Architecture: any
Provides: hpklinux-module
Depends: hpklinux-utils, kernel-image-_KVERS_ | linux-image-_KVERS_
Description: hpklinux module for linux (kernel _KVERS_)
 This package contains the kernel module for the linux kernel driver to allow
 AudioScience cards to be controlled using the HPI API.  This API is documented
 in http://www.audioscience.com/internet/download/spchpi.pdf
 .
 please see /usr/share/doc/hpklinux-module-_KVERS_ for details.
 .
 This package contains the compiled kernel module for _KVERS_
 .
 If you have compiled your own kernel, you will most likely need to build
 your own hpklinux-module.  The hpklinux-source package has been
 provided for use with the Debian kernel-package utility to produce a version
 of hpklinux-module for your kernel.
